content: So the nature is that within time, we see a larger amount of such larger deals, which are normally I would say, characterized by -- if I call it our first of all large, I mean, seven -- high-end six, seven, and even eight digits, they are typical to strategic accounts. We've seen a little bit higher-than-expected turnover, which does impact especially with larger customers, some delays in the execution of the deals not the disappearing of the deals or disappearing of the budget, which is very natural, I would say in such environment.
